The conformers of compounds 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, and 11 after conformational analyses were optimised using DFT at the PBE0-D3(BJ)/def2-SVP level in MeOH using the polarizable conductor calculation model (SMD) by applying the ORCA4.2.1 program (

, 

). The energies, oscillator strengths, and rotational strengths (velocity) of the first 60 electronic excitations were calculated using the TDDFT methodology at the CAM-B3LYP/def2-TZVP level in MeOH. The ECD spectra were simulated by applying the overlapping Gaussian function (half the bandwidth at 1/e peak height, sigma = 0.30, for all) (

). To get the final spectra, the simulated spectra of the conformers were averaged according to Boltzmann distribution theory based on the relative Gibbs free energy (
ΔG
) of the conformers.

The NMR shielding constants were computed after geometry optimisation using the gauge-including atomic orbital (GIAO) method at the mPW1PW91/6-311G** level in PCM MeOH using the Gaussian 09 program (

). The Boltzmann weights were computed using the relative free energies at the wB97M-V/def2-TZVP level in SMD MeOH using ORCA. The shielding constants were applied in the DP4+ probability analysis (

). The linear correlation coefficient (

R 
2

) and DP4+ probability were used to evaluate the deviation between the experimental and calculated results.

